SIMPLE: swill
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swill
<hw>Swill</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Swilled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Swilling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>swilen</ets> to wash,
AS. <ets>swilian</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To wash; to
drench.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As fearfully as doth a galled rock⟦br⟧
O'erhang and jutty his confounded base,⟦br⟧
<qex>Swilled</qex> with the wild and wasteful ocean.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Properly, to drink like a pig. See <er>Swill</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>To drink in great draughts; to swallow
greedily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Well-dressed people, of both sexes, . . . devouring sliced beef,
and <qex>swilling</qex> pork, and punch, and cider.</q>
<rj><qau>Smollett.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To inebriate; to fill with drink.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I should be loth⟦br⟧
To meet the rudeness and <qex>swilled</qex> insolence⟦br⟧
Of such late wassailers.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swill</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swill
<hw>Swill</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To drink greedily or swinishly; to
drink to excess.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swill</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Swill
<hw>Swill</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The wash, or mixture of
liquid substances, given to swine; hogwash; -- called also
<altname>swillings</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Large draughts of liquor; drink taken in excessive
quantities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swiller</ent>⟦br⟧
